## Established Contracts (Do Not Re-Derive)

These contracts were locked in previous sprints. Treat them as stable API:

### Hero intent/decision (game/sim/contracts.py)
- `HeroDecisionRecord(action, reason, at_ms, context)` with `.to_dict(age_ms)`
- `HeroIntentSnapshot(intent, last_decision)` with `.to_dict(now_ms)`
- `hero.intent: str` — intent taxonomy label ("idle", "pursuing_bounty", "engaging_enemy", etc.)
- `hero.last_decision: HeroDecisionRecord | None`
- `hero.get_intent_snapshot(now_ms=None) -> dict` — UI/QA-safe accessor, no AI imports

### Bounty eval (game/systems/bounty.py)
- `bounty.responders: int` — hero count pursuing this bounty
- `bounty.attractiveness_score: float`
- `bounty.attractiveness_tier: str` — "low" / "med" / "high" (deterministic)
- `BountySystem.update_metrics(heroes, game_state)` — call once per tick before HUD render

### Combat gating (game/entities/hero.py)
- `hero.can_attack: bool` — hard gate; combat system must check before dealing damage
- `hero.attack_blocked_reason: str` — "inside_building", "resting", "dead", etc.

### Stuck signals (game/entities/hero.py)
- `hero.stuck_active: bool`
- `hero.stuck_since_ms: int | None` — sim-time ms
- `hero.last_progress_ms: int` — sim-time ms
- `hero.unstuck_attempts: int` — monotonic counter
- `hero.stuck_reason: str`
- `hero.get_stuck_snapshot(now_ms=None) -> dict` — UI/QA-safe accessor

### Display mode (game/engine.py)
- `engine.apply_display_settings(display_mode: str, window_size: tuple | None)` — "fullscreen" / "borderless" / "windowed"
- `game_state["display_mode"]` and `game_state["window_size"]` — for Agent 08's Graphics menu
- Settings are UI-only; no sim state, no wall-clock

### Timebase rule (non-negotiable)
- All sim-time access: `game.sim.timebase.now_ms()`
- Never: `time.time()`, `pygame.time.get_ticks()` in sim logic

